    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1965-04-12T15:46:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1965-04-12T15:46:00-05:00" n="602"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d602">
                <head>602. Telegram From the <gloss type="from">Department of State</gloss> to the
                        <gloss type="to">Embassy in South Africa</gloss>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d602fn1">Source: Department of State, Central
                        Files, DEF 7 S AFR–US. Confidential; Priority. Drafted by Meyers; cleared by
                        Captain Coward in OPNAV, Williams, and <persName corresp="#p_HPJ2"
                            >Hooper</persName>; and approved by <persName corresp="#p_KJC1"
                            >Kitchen</persName>. Sent to Cape Town, and repeated to Pretoria.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1965-04-12T15:46:00-05:00">April 12, 1965, 3:46 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>111. Joint State-Defense message. Re: Visit USS Independence (Capetown’s
                        129).<note n="2" xml:id="d602fn2">Dated April 7. (Ibid.)</note> Appreciate
                        <gloss target="#t_SAG1">SAG</gloss> clearance of visit USS Independence.
                    Number of flights from Independence to Capetown involving landing onshore will
                    be few, and generally limited to those necessary to assure in advance of
                    Independence docking all necessary actions have been taken to facilitate mooring
                    of ship, handling mail, etc.</p>
                <pb facs="1070" n="1022" xml:id="pg_1022"/>
                <p>In informing <gloss target="#t_SAG1">SAG</gloss> of foregoing, however, you
                    should indicate to Duplooy USG cannot accept any stipulation regarding
                    utilization crew members including any which would result in racial segregation.
                    If <gloss target="#t_SAG1">SAG</gloss> should make such a condition of visits US
                    will have to plan its Naval operations to exclude calls in Republic.</p>
                <p>Ship’s aircraft including helicopters will of course refrain from taking
                    photographs of military establishments and their immediate environment in Cape
                    peninsula area as requested.</p>
                <p>Further details should be handled by Embassy Naval Attache through establishment
                    channels, as indicated <gloss target="#t_Deptel1">Deptel</gloss> 67.<note n="3"
                        xml:id="d602fn3">Dated February 25. (Ibid.)</note>
                </p>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_FYI1">FYI</gloss>. We recognize visit of vessel such as
                    Independence bound stimulate public interest, as noted Embassy’s 130.<note n="4"
                        xml:id="d602fn4">Dated April 8. (Ibid.)</note> Will provide press guidance
                    as soon as possible.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_RD3">
                            <hi rend="strong">Rusk</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
